{"info": {"author": "Christophe Catherine Slychan", "author_email": "krzysztof.slychan@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Framework :: Flask", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Topic :: System :: Hardware :: Hardware Drivers"], "description": "# hifipower\n\nhigh fidelity equipment power controller daemon\n-----------------------------------------------\n\nA daemon running on an Orange Pi or RPi, exposing a web API for switching the audio equipment on or off, using a relay connected with one of the GPIO pins.\n\nThis software reads a configuration file (``/etc/hifipowerd.conf``) and gets the pin numbers for shutdown and reboot buttons, automatic mode sense and relay drive output. Then the web API is started, exposing three endpoints:\n\n``address/hifi/power`` (GET) - get the current state as JSON,\n\n``address/hifi/power/on`` (GET) - turns the power on,\n\n``address/hifi/power/off`` (GET) - turns the power off.\n\nFuture features\n---------------\n\nUse PulseAudio or ALSA to detect lack of audio signal on the input (configurable), then if no audio is present for a preset time (e.g. 10 minutes), turn the equipment off automatically. Prevents idle power draw by e.g. vacuum tube amplifiers.", "description_content_type": "", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "http://github.com/elegantandrogyne/hifipower", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "hifipower", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/hifipower/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/hifipower/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "http://github.com/elegantandrogyne/hifipower"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/hifipower/0.1b7/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "On/off control via web API for hi-fi audio equipment", "version": "0.1b7", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p># hifipower</p>\n<div id=\"high-fidelity-equipment-power-controller-daemon\">\n<h2>high fidelity equipment power controller daemon</h2>\n<p>A daemon running on an Orange Pi or RPi, exposing a web API for switching the audio equipment on or off, using a relay connected with one of the GPIO pins.</p>\n<p>This software reads a configuration file (<tt>/etc/hifipowerd.conf</tt>) and gets the pin numbers for shutdown and reboot buttons, automatic mode sense and relay drive output. Then the web API is started, exposing three endpoints:</p>\n<p><tt>address/hifi/power</tt> (GET) - get the current state as JSON,</p>\n<p><tt>address/hifi/power/on</tt> (GET) - turns the power on,</p>\n<p><tt>address/hifi/power/off</tt> (GET) - turns the power off.</p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"future-features\">\n<h2>Future features</h2>\n<p>Use PulseAudio or ALSA to detect lack of audio signal on the input (configurable), then if no audio is present for a preset time (e.g. 10 minutes), turn the equipment off automatically. Prevents idle power draw by e.g. vacuum tube amplifiers.</p>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 5726910, "releases": {"0.1a1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "33c610a27ecaea1b08c9bb33df19d699", "sha256": "24e6990fd3b15ddfb4ed618a8f8061f5e4d5d789d3dbe7e6dc06671d9689660f"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "hifipower-0.1a1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "33c610a27ecaea1b08c9bb33df19d699", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 4341, "upload_time": "2019-08-24T14:21:11", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-08-24T14:21:11.044640Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/f6/bd/335ace68273b3e6480e5346ce4e284269e42b0bc52febb37231ab795f18f/hifipower-0.1a1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1a2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "554ca0e6c3d30d85055261